    "original_title": "Manhattan: Pleasant Avenue - 117th Street",
    "text": "(1)\n330 Pleasant Ave., east side, between 117th and 118th Streets. This building is an old house which has been used for a dozen or more years as a Settlement House (The Neighborhood House), of the Church Extension Committee of the Presbytery of New York and is now being given up. July 13, 1927.\n\nP. L. Sperr.\n\n(2)\nThe same, five years later.\n1932.\n\nJ. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York. Negative No. 252.\n",
